type: scenario
name: kaijo/ssh-max-auth-exceeded-pfsense
description: >
  Detects SSH connections that are aborted after exceeding the maximum number
  of authentication attempts on pfSense systems. This event is generated by
  OpenSSH when multiple failed login attempts occur within a single session,
  making it a strong indicator of brute-force activity. Fully aligned with
  FreeBSD/OpenSSH log formats used by pfSense CE/Plus.

author: kaijo
license: MIT
version: 0.1.7

labels:
  service: sshd
  platform: pfSense
  attack_type: bruteforce
  confidence: high

tags:
  - pfSense
  - SSH
  - Security
  - Bruteforce
  - FreeBSD
  - OpenSSH

events:
  - authentication_failed
  - bruteforce
